    dc:title "The discovery of new Chilean taxa revolutionizes the systematics of Geoplaninae Neotropical land planarians (Platyhelminthes: Tricladida)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7814061>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7814063>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7814067>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7814069>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7814071> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7814061>
    dc:description "Figure 40. Sarcoplana musculosa sp. nov. Photographs of living holotype. A, dorsal view, while creeping. B, dorsal view, at rest. C, ventral view. Scale bars not available. The specimen is more or less 18 mm long at rest." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7814061/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7814063>
    dc:description "Figure 41. Sarcoplana musculosa sp. nov. Photomicrographs of histological sections. A, transverse section at 0.88 µm from the anterior tip of the body showing one sensory depression (arrow). B, C, transverse sections of the pre-pharyngeal region. D, E, horizontal sections of the dorsal (B) and ventral (C) portions behind the cephalic region. F, transverse section at 1.9 mm from anterior tip of the body." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7814063/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7814067>
    dc:description "Figure 42. Sarcoplana musculosa sp. nov. A–D, photomicrographs of transverse sections of the anterior section of the body, at 600, 400, 200 and 160 µm from the anterior extremity, respectively. Same scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7814067/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7814069>
    dc:description "Figure 43. Sarcoplana musculosa sp. nov. A, diagrammatic representation of the pharynx from sagittal sections. B, photomicrograph of a sagittal section through the pharynx and copulatory apparatus. C, diagrammatic representation of the copulatory apparatus. Red and blue colours indicate regions with gland cells producing erythrophil and cyanophil secretion, respectively." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7814069/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7814071>
    dc:description "Figure 44. Sarcoplana musculosa sp. nov. Photomicrographs of sagittal sections. A, copulatory apparatus. B, anterior musculoglandular organ. C, posterior musculoglandular organ and female atrium. D, female atrium." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7814071/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

